 Coursera Society, Networks and Information Michael Kearns '),(41,'Securing Digital Democracy',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Society, Networks and Information',' Securing Digital Democracy Coursera Society, Networks and Information J. Alex Halderman In this course, you\'ll learn what every citizen should know about the security risks--and future potential &mdash; of electronic voting and Internet voting. University of Michigan'),(42,'Social Network Analysis',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Society, Networks and Information',' Social Network Analysis Coursera Society, Networks and Information Lada Adamic This course will use social network analysis, both its theory and computational tools, to make sense of the social and information networks that have been fueled and rendered accessible by the internet. University of Michigan'),(43,'Algorithms, Part I',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Computer Science',' Algorithms, Part I Coursera Computer Science Robert Sedgewick Kevin Wayne '),(44,'Algorithms, Part II',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Computer Science',' Algorithms, Part II Coursera Computer Science Robert Sedgewick Kevin Wayne This course covers the essential information that every serious programmer needs to know about algorithms and data structures, with emphasis on applications and scientific performance analysis of Java implementations. Princeton University'),(45,'Computer Vision: From 3D Reconstruction to Visual Recognition',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Computer Science',' Computer Vision: From 3D Reconstruction to Visual Recognition Coursera Computer Science Silvio Savarese Fei-Fei Li This course delivers a systematic overview of computer vision, emphasizing two key issues in modeling vision: space and meaning. We will study the fundamental theories and important algorithms of computer vision together, starting from the analysis of 2D images, and culminating in the holistic understanding of a 3D scene. Stanford University University of Michigan'),(46,'Computer Architecture',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Compute