,'Coursera','Humanities and Social Sciences',' Fantasy and Science Fiction: The Human Mind, Our Modern World Coursera Humanities and Social Sciences Eric Rabkin '),(57,'Greek and Roman Mythology',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Humanities and Social Sciences',' Greek and Roman Mythology Coursera Humanities and Social Sciences Peter Struck This course will focus on the myths of ancient Greece and Rome, as a way of exploring the nature of myth and the function it plays for individuals, societies, and nations. University of Pennsylvania'),(58,'Introduction to Sociology',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Humanities and Social Sciences',' Introduction to Sociology Coursera Humanities and Social Sciences Mitchell Duneier '),(59,'Listening to World Music',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Humanities and Social Sciences',' Listening to World Music Coursera Humanities and Social Sciences Carol Muller '),(60,'Modern & Contemporary American Poetry',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Humanities and Social Sciences',' Modern & Contemporary American Poetry Coursera Humanities and Social Sciences Al Filreis This course is a fast-paced introduction to modern and contemporary U.S. poetry, from Dickinson and Whitman to the present. Participants (who need no prior experience with poetry) will learn how to read poems that are supposedly \"difficult.\" University of Pennsylvania'),(61,'Software Engineering for SaaS',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Computer Science',' Software Engineering for SaaS Coursera Computer Science Armando Fox David Patterson '),(62,'Design and Analysis of Algorithms I (re-run)',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Computer Science',' Design and Analysis of Algorithms I (re-run) Coursera Computer Science Tim Roughgarden '),(63,'Networks: Friends, Money, and Bytes',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Society, Networks and Information',' Networks: Friends, Money, and Bytes Coursera Society, Networks and Information Mung Chiang A course driven by 20 practical questions about wireless, web, and the Internet, about how products from companies like Appl