s and answers to common questions that parents have about vaccines. University of Pennsylvania'),(204,'Fundamentals of Pharmacology',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Healthcare, Medicine, and Biology',' Fundamentals of Pharmacology Coursera Healthcare, Medicine, and Biology Emma Meagher In this class you will learn how drugs affect the body, how they alter disease processes and how they might produce toxicity. We will discuss how new drugs are tested and developed prior to them being used for patient care. We will describe how personalization of medicine will become a common day reality in patient care. University of Pennsylvania'),(205,'Introduction to Finance',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Economics & Finance',' Introduction to Finance Coursera Economics & Finance Gautam Kaul This course will introduce you to frameworks and tools to measure value; both for corporate and personal assets. It will also help you in decision-making, again at both the corporate and personal levels. University of Michigan'),(206,'Fantasy and Science Fiction: The Human Mind, Our Modern World',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Humanities and Social Sciences',' Fantasy and Science Fiction: The Human Mind, Our Modern World Coursera Humanities and Social Sciences Eric Rabkin We understand the world â€” and our selves â€” through stories. Then some of those hopes and fears become the world. University of Michigan'),(207,'Internet History, Technology, and Security',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Society, Networks and Information',' Internet History, Technology, and Security Coursera Society, Networks and Information Charles Severance What is the Internet? How was it created? How does it work? University of Michigan'),(208,'Quantum Mechanics and Quantum Computation',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Computer Science',' Quantum Mechanics and Quantum Computation Coursera Computer Science Umesh Vazirani This is an introduction to quantum computation, a cutting edge field that tries to exploit the exponential power of computers based on quantum mechanics. The course does not assume any prior background in quantum mechanics, and can be viewed as a very simple and conceptual introduction to that field. University of California, Berkeley'),(209,'Health Informatics in the Cloud',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Health and Society & Medical Ethics',' Health Informatics in the Cloud Coursera Health and Society & Medical Ethics Mark Braunstein A non-technical introduction to the contemporary application of computing to healthcare delivery, public health and community-based clinical research. Georgia Institute of Technology'),(210,'Accountable Talk®: Conversation that Works',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Humanities and Social Sciences',' Accountable Talk®: Conversation that Works Coursera Humanities and Social Sciences Lauren Resnick, Ed.D., Jennifer Zoltners Sherer, Ph.D. Designed for teachers and learners in every setting - in school and out, in formal learning environments or at home - this course is an introduction to the theory and practice of well-structured talk that builds the mind. University of Pittsburgh'),(211,'Nutrition and Physical Activity for Health',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Medicine',' Nutrition and Physical Activity for Health Coursera Medicine John M. Jakicic, Ph.D., Amy D. Rickman, Ph.D., RD, LDN This course will provide a coherent, understandable look at the evidence on how nutrition and physical activity impact health through lower morbidity, longevity, and quality of life. University of Pittsburgh'),(212,'A Look at Nuclear Science and Technology',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Physical & Earth Sciences',' A Look at Nuclear Science and Technology Coursera Physical & Earth Sciences Larry Foulke This course will focus on the theory, design and operation of commercial nuclear power reactors. The course will also touch on contemporary issues regarding nuclear power generation including: the nuclear fuel cycle, the economics of nuclear power, and nuclear non-proliferation. University of Pittsburgh'),(213,'Clinical Terminology for International Students',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Medicine',' Clinical Terminology for International Students Coursera Medicine Valerie Swigart, Ph.D., RN, Michael Gold, Ph.D. This course is for undergraduate or graduate students in the health professions who are English language learners and who are planning or currently experiencing clinical practice education in the United States.   University of Pittsburgh'),(214,'Disaster Preparedness',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Medicine',' Disaster Preparedness Coursera Medicine Michael Beach During this course, students will gain an understanding of the Disaster Cycle, concentrating on the Mitigation Phase. They will examine disaster planning on a personal level developing a disaster plan and examine Awareness and Attitude during disasters and daily life. University of Pittsburgh'),(215,'Women and the Civil Rights Movement',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Humanities and Social Sciences',' Women and the Civil Rights Movement Coursera Humanities and Social Sciences Dr. Elsa Barkley Brown Learn about womenâ€™s roles in the U.S. civil rights struggles of the 1890s to the 1990s.  University of Maryland, College Park'),(216,'Developing Innovative Ideas for New Companies',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Economics & Finance',' Developing Innovative Ideas for New Companies Coursera Economics & Finance Dr. James V. Green Explore how to identify and develop great ideas into great companies. Learn how to identify opportunities based on real customer needs. Develop solid business models. Create successful companies. University of Maryland, College Park'),(217,'Fundamentals of Personal Financial Planning',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Economics & Finance',' Fundamentals of Personal Financial Planning Coursera Economics & Finance Don DeBok Explore the basic personal financial planning concepts.  Learn how to define and reach your financial goals. Apply the framework of personal financial planning to monitor your own finances, with special emphasis on lifecycle-specific topics, such as saving for education, student loans, or wealth management and estate planning. University of California, Irvine'),(218,'Animal Behaviour',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Biology & Life Sciences',' Animal Behaviour Coursera Biology & Life Sciences Raoul Mulder Mark Elgar This course will help you understand the remarkable behaviors of wild animals from an evolutionary perspective.&nbsp;\n\n\n[Image: Peacock spider. Photo by JÃ¼rgen Otto] University of Melbourne'),(219,'Epigenetic Control of Gene Expression',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Medicine',' Epigenetic Control of Gene Expression Coursera Medicine Dr Marnie Blewitt Each mammalian cell has the same genes, yet performs distinct functions. This is achieved by epigenetic control of gene expression; the switching on and switching off of genes. This course will cover the principles of epigenetic control of gene expression, how epigenetic control contributes to cellular differentiation and development, and how it goes wrong in disease. University of Melbourne'),(220,'Discrete Optimization',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Computer Science: Artificial Intelligence, Robotics, Vision',' Discrete Optimization Coursera Computer Science: Artificial Intelligence, Robotics, Vision Professor Pascal Van Hentenryck Tired of solving Sudokus by hand? This class teaches you how to solve complex search problems with discrete optimization, including constraint programming, local search, and mixed-integer programming. University of Melbourne'),(221,'Principles of Macroeconomics',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Economics & Finance',' Principles of Macroeconomics Coursera Economics & Finance Professor Nilss Olekalns  All of us are affected by macroeconomic forces â€“ they shape the very world we live in. And governments all around the world try to shape those forces in ways that (hopefully) improve the lives of their constituents. In this subject, we will examine the major theories used by macro economists to analyse national economies and the international economy.  