, and Audio Engineering Loudon Stearns Learn about the music production processâ€”including recording, editing, and mixingâ€”and the tools available to you to create contemporary music on your computer.  Berklee College of Music'),(259,'Linear and Discrete Optimization',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Computer Science: Theory',' Linear and Discrete Optimization Coursera Computer Science: Theory Friedrich Eisenbrand The course is an introduction to linear and discrete optimization - an important part of computational mathematics with a wide range of applications in many areas of everyday life. Ã‰cole Polytechnique FÃ©dÃ©rale de Lausanne'),(260,'Financial Engineering and Risk Management',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Economics & Finance',' Financial Engineering and Risk Management Coursera Economics & Finance Martin Haugh Garud Iyengar, with guest lectures by Emanuel Derman This course is an introduction to the theory and practice of financial engineering and risk management. We consider the pricing of derivatives, portfolio optimization and risk management and cast a critical eye on how these are used in practice. Columbia University'),(261,'Natural Language Processing',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Computer Science',' Natural Language Processing Coursera Computer Science Michael Collins Have you ever wondered how to build a system that automatically translates between languages? Or a system that can understand natural language instructions from a human?  This class will cover the fundamentals of mathematical and computational models of language, and the application of these models to key problems in natural language processing. Columbia University'),(262,'Climate Literacy: Navigating Climate Conversations',NULL,NULL,'Coursera','Physical & Earth Sciences',' Climate Literacy: Navigating Climate Conversations Coursera Physical & Earth Sciences Sarah Burch Tom-Pierre Frappé-Sénéclauze Climate Literacy tackles the scientific and socio-political dimensions of climate change. This course introduces